commentTextItems.html: Pakistan keep the series alive! Tossed up outside off and he reaches out and drives him wide of the diving point fielder

commentPostTextItems.html: Presentation: The endless stream of awards continue...
Nasir Jamshed is the Man of the Match: "I was cramping towards the end. The captain told me to play my natural game."
Clarke: "I should have bowled first. Good third game coming up. Difficult to hold onto the ball but no excuses. Our middle order played well but we didn't execute with the ball."
Misbah: "Much needed win. Jamshed showed maturity and class. Bowlers did a wonderful job to restrict them. In this outfield it is difficult to restrict any team under 250, lucky toss to lose."
That's it from us here. It's been a really really long night. Goes without saying really. Catch the decider in Sharjah on Monday. Thanks for your mails. Cheers!

End of match: Pakistan enhance their good chasing record at Abu Dhabi. It was Clarke who won the toss and opted to bat, but it backfired because the dew was uncontrollable for the bowlers late at night.

Having said that, a deserved victory for Pakistan. A crucial DRS reversal proved the turning point as Jamshed wisely challenged the LBW early in the innings and went on to score an entertaining 97. He should never have been given out in the first place. Azhar Ali played with a relaxed frame of mind and Pakistan never looked in danger of folding up. Stay with us for the presentation.

commentTextItems.html: tossed up on the off stump and he drills it across the line and past midwicket, Mike Hussey charges from square leg and cuts it off
that's a neat slog, tossed up on the off stump and he gets on his knee and whams it high over midwicket, one bounce and four
drifts on the pads and he clips it to deep square leg
keeps it outside off and Misbah opts to leave it alone

commentPostTextItems.html: Morfi has an alternative view: "The lesson here is not just that they should not play cricket in humid conditions, but that teams should fulfil their cricketing commitments when and where they are due,  so that such tournaments dont need to be squeezed in. It is a greater lesson for Australia to learn and rightly so."

dismissalText.commentary: David Warner lbw b Saeed Ajmal 24 (68b 2x4 0x6 89m) SR: 35.29

dismissalComment.html: and the long, long vigil comes to an end! Pitching on the leg and middle, hitting on the pad and struck low on the pads. Ticks all the boxes required to dole out an LBW decision. Ajmal is ecstatic. Warner is asked,by his captain, if he wants to use the referral, but he refuses it

dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke lbw b Mohammad Hafeez 37 (54b 3x4 0x6 92m) SR: 68.51

dismissalComment.html: Clarke's been given lbw and he is reviewing it, lands quite wide outside off and spins back in sharply and hits the top flap of his pad, umpire Llong gave him out and Clarke asked for it to be reviewed because it was a question of the height, replays showed the ball just clipping the top of leg stump, Llong's decision stands

dismissalText.commentary: David Hussey lbw b Saeed Ajmal 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Pakistan have struck with two lbws in quick succession! Hussey looked a bit surprised, he was a long way across his stumps and hence exposed the leg stump and a part of middle, the ball spun back in and hit him low on the pads, umpire Ahsan Raza was convinced, Australia have already used up their review

dismissalText.commentary: Dan Christian c Nasir Jamshed b Junaid Khan 18 (15b 2x4 0x6 19m) SR: 120

dismissalComment.html: that was a sharp catch by Jamshed! Christian fetched that from outside off and pulled it flat and fast towards deep midwicket, Jamshed ran across to his right and plucked the ball on the dive

headshotImage.longCaption: Junaid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Johnson b Junaid Khan 2 (7b 0x4 0x6 16m) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: ends his spell with two wickets in as many balls! Junaid bowled that full and straight on the stumps, Johnson had a wild swing and missed it completely, crashed onto off and middle

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c MEK Hussey b Christian 23 (27b 2x4 0x6 58m) SR: 85.18

dismissalComment.html: Hafeez has fallen for the trap! There was a fielder at deep square leg and he hit it straight to him, it was short outside off and Hafeez chose to club it across the line, ended up pulling it flat and Mike Hussey did well to catch it on the fall, the wet ball could so easily have slipped out

dismissalText.commentary: Nasir Jamshed c Starc b Johnson 97 (98b 11x4 2x6 152m) SR: 98.97

dismissalComment.html: he's fallen three short of a century! Johnson pitched it up outside the off stump, Jamshed wanted to clear the infield again on seeing mid-off up, didn't time it at all and didn't get the elevation, tamely chipped it to Starc who took it easily falling forward at mid-off
